-- Death Toll From Typhoon in Guangdong Province Rises to 33, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-22T17:34:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/death-toll-from-typhoon-in-guangdong-province-rises-to-33-xinhua-reports.html
The death toll from flooding and
landslides caused by Typhoon Fanapi increased to 33, with 42
people missing, Xinhua news agency said, citing the provincial
flood-control headquarters.  More than 1 million people were affected by the disaster,
which forced the evacuation of 78,400 people in low-lying areas,
Xinhua said. More than 1,400 homes and more than 30,000 hectares
of crops were destroyed, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  